This example includes the basic functionality for adding, removing, and marking tasks as complete, as well as saving tasks to localStorage so that they persist even after page reloads.

Project Structure
HTML - Basic structure of the page.
CSS - Styles to make the application visually appealing.
JavaScript - Logic for adding, removing, marking as complete, and saving tasks to localStorage.

Code Description
HTML: Defines the basic structure of the application, including a form for adding tasks and a list for displaying tasks.
CSS: Applies simple styles to the interface, making it pleasant and easy to use.
JavaScript:
Listens to the DOMContentLoaded event to load saved tasks when the page loads.
Adds a submit event to the form for adding new tasks.
Functions for adding, removing, and marking tasks as complete.
Uses localStorage to save and load tasks, ensuring that they persist after page reloads.